column5: We caught a few big ones yesterday. Catch & Released            Just wondering how many pounds a 19" Largemouth Bass would be.
nice bass..
Nice bass !! I'm just ball parking it....If the fish was a football I'd put it at about 5 lbs but on average I'd say 3 to 4 lbs.
close to 4 lbs, real good fish   you don't sell electronic on eBay, do you.....you don't have to answer if you don't want to
My guess on that fish would be around 5. I don't worry much about weight, but do measure length of large fish. Length tell you how big a fish is, weight tells you how well it's been eating
4.2 pounds
Four..ish !!
yep right around 4lbs nice bucket
Glad to see your gave Mr.Bass the white glove treatment!!!  4
4LBS 1oz
I would but her about 4  Cheers!
4.35lbs but if ya have rely long arms you might get 6.7lbs out of a pic
Yes, we sell electronic on eBay and we repair all type of electronic device, including Fishfinder, GPS, inboard/outboard motors.
2.9lbs
dang, I have bought a bunch of stuff from you
Maybe you should buy a boat from him then.LOL  Nice fish
3 lbs
Agreed
just need a motor and an engine
Nice fish and FYI, so far, our panel of expert judges have put that fine specimen at 3.9071 lbs. You just can't get more accurate than that. Talk about electronic scales...

lol. love it,  You even went to the nearest ten thousandths!!
